biography.content: Professor Martin Holt leads the Gay Community Periodic Surveys, a key part of Australia's behavioural surveillance system for HIV, and the PrEPARE Project, a longitudinal study of gay and bisexual men's attitudes to biomedical HIV prevention. The Gay Community Periodic Surveys are supported by NHMRC Partnership Project funding (2021-26).
